{
  "text": "We reported a case of adult-onset NM with progressive HF. The clinical and pathological findings of our patient were similar to those of previously described cases of adultonset nemaline myopathy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] including proximal muscle weakness, dysphagia, lack of familiarity involvement or preceding symptoms and monoclonal gammopathy. Symptomatic hypotension significantly limited optimal titration of Angiotensin Converting Enzyme (ACE)-inhibitors and mostly of beta-blockers with a consequent persistent elevated resting HR.",
